in the book that these may be copies

01:07:22.380 --> 01:07:26.860
from the 18th century of something
that was genuinely earlier

01:07:26.860 --> 01:07:29.720
because certainly the handwriting
suggests something that was written

01:07:29.720 --> 01:07:32.210
after the time of Marco Polo.

01:07:32.210 --> 01:07:34.300
There's not been a lot
of testing of the inks.

01:07:34.300 --> 01:07:37.550
There has been some
testing of the velum.

01:07:37.550 --> 01:07:41.800 position:56%
But these may be something where it
was genuinely a manuscript tradition

01:07:41.800 --> 01:07:45.940
trying to preserve
genuinely anomalous maps,

01:07:45.940 --> 01:07:50.120
but there are many oddities,
there are anachronisms in terms

01:07:50.120 --> 01:07:53.680
of the representation, you
know, this far northeast

01:07:53.680 --> 01:07:57.430
that doesn't appear on
any maps of this period.

01:07:57.430 --> 01:08:01.990 position:56%
But obviously I felt that there were
a number of distinctive features

01:08:01.990 --> 01:08:07.930 position:56%
which merited 13 years of my life to
study these maps, and then the sort

01:08:07.930 --> 01:08:11.850 position:56%
of last lesson that I like to say is
that the critics, for those of you

01:08:11.850 --> 01:08:16.290
who plan to write books,
critics are never satisfied.

01:08:16.290 --> 01:08:19.450
