01:52:33.630 --> 01:52:37.700
to the Library and when the group
of things came to the Library

01:52:37.700 --> 01:52:40.590
and Ben said they were
analyzed, and we'll pull this

01:52:40.590 --> 01:52:45.840
out when we show it tomorrow,
the FBI crime lab is the people

01:52:45.840 --> 01:52:47.570
who did the investigation.

01:52:47.570 --> 01:52:50.750
And J. Edgar Hoover,
there's correspondence,

01:52:50.750 --> 01:52:52.500
that he's very worried
about this map

01:52:52.500 --> 01:52:56.670
as being a national security issue
because if it does in fact show

01:52:56.670 --> 01:53:00.670
that the Chinese or Marco Polo
or someone knew about America,

01:53:00.670 --> 01:53:03.010 position:56%
this would overturn western history,

01:53:03.010 --> 01:53:07.510
and so there's a letter here
form J. Edgar Hoover announcing

01:53:07.510 --> 01:53:10.590
that they are going to do
everything they can to study it.

01:53:10.590 --> 01:53:17.000
And so it's kind of a fascinating,
the power of maps really

01:53:17.000 --> 01:53:19.630
in this collection, in
the Vinland collection

01:53:19.630 --> 01:53:23.770
and with Stephanie's workshops,
you can see the amazing power

01:53:23.770 --> 01:53:29.340
of these images in a cultural and
legal sense that the authenticity

01:53:29.340 --> 01:53:31.440
and truth of them doesn't
really matter.

01:53:31.440 --> 01:53:34.080
It's just they have
these profound effects.

01:53:34.080 --> 01:53:38.010
